name: Well 80 Artesian Brewing
vibe: Home of Artie and built on the Artesian Well
insiderVibe: It's slick. Maybe too slick? It feels like a brewpub, not a bar—lots of polished concrete and big screens. But you can't argue with the history. Tapping that well is a boss move, and the 'Leopold's #1 Lager' is legit respect to the old school. It's where you go to watch the game, not to hide from the world.
originStory: They literally drilled a hole in the floor to tap into the same mythical aquifer that made Olympia Beer famous in 1896. It's a shiny, high-energy brewpub built directly on top of history, serving crisp lagers made from the 'Water' that put this town on the map.
address: 514 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
historySnippet: Taste the water (literally) from the original Artesian Well.

flashBounties.title: $2 Pretzels & Cheese
flashBounties.description: Flash Bounty: $2 Pretzels valid for next 45 mins.

fullMenu.name: Leopold's #1 Lager
fullMenu.description: The original 1896 recipe. Crisp, clean, and historic.

fullMenu.name: Volcanic Ash IPA
fullMenu.description: Hazy, juicy, and explosive. Citra and Mosaic hops.

fullMenu.name: Darkness Imperial Stout
fullMenu.description: Aged in bourbon barrels. Thick, chocolatey, and dangerous.

fullMenu.name: Truffle Fries
fullMenu.description: Crispy fries, parmesan, truffle oil, garlic aioli.

fullMenu.name: Seasonal Sour
fullMenu.description: Rotating seasonal fruit sour. Ask server for details.

name: Ilk Lodge
vibe: Twin Peaks meets Skate Rat
insiderVibe: Pat Jansen is a legend. He ran the brewing at Three Mags, then Matchless, now this. The vibe is 'Twin Peaks meets Skate Rat.' It's cool without trying. And the burgers? Greasy, smashy perfection. This is the soul of downtown brewing.
originStory: The former brewers of Matchless and Three Magnets took over this iconic corner. Now it's a 'lodge' serving high-technique ales and arguably the best smash burgers in the county, resurrecting an iconic spot in Olympia nightlife.
address: 515 Jefferson St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Three Magnets Brewing Co.
vibe: The Community Hub & NA Pioneers
insiderVibe: The center of the 'Sober Squad' league track. Home of 'Self Care' non-alcoholic beer and Scherler Sundays.
originStory: Sara and Nate Reilly built a 'Third Place' for Olympia. Their pivot to 'Self Care' (a non-alcoholic line) has made them a national player in the sober-curious movement.
address: 600 Franklin St SE STE 105, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Whitewood Cider Co.
vibe: The Teeny Tiny Taproom
insiderVibe: The Teeny Tiny Taproom is the definition of cool. It's barely a room. You sit on the patio, you drink cider that tastes like actual apples, not candy. It's legit. No frills, just product.
originStory: Dave White was writing about cider before anyone was drinking it. He founded the Northwest Cider Association and then put his money where his mouth was, creating a 'Teeny Tiny Taproom' in downtown Oly that is smaller than most walk-in closets but pours the most respected heirloom ciders in the state. They recently moved production to Tenino, but the heart remains in that tiny room on 4th Ave.
address: 728 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA

name: Endless Sound Cellars
vibe: The Urban Cellar
insiderVibe: A sleek, industrial cellar feel inside the 222 Market. Perfect for a sophisticated evening flight.
originStory: Mark Bosso brought his winemaking chops from Woodinville to the heart of downtown Olympia. It's the perfect 'urban winery' experience.
address: 222 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Matchless Brewing
vibe: The Hype Beast; 80s Synth-Pop Vibes
insiderVibe: The branding is incredible. Best cans in the county. The vibe in the taproom is industrial but energetic. It feels like a place where beer nerds congregate. It's legit.
originStory: Born from the creative minds of Three Magnets alumni, Matchless exploded onto the scene with branding that looks like an 80s synth-pop album cover and beer that pushes every boundary. They don't just make IPAs; they make hazy, juicy, complex hop-bombs that win awards and wreck palates in the best way possible.
address: 8036 River Dr SE #208, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Triceratops Brewing Company
vibe: Approachably dangerous, family founded
insiderVibe: The Strawberry Golden is a gateway drug for my wine drinkers. It's sophisticated enough, not cloyingly sweet. It allows a wine drinker to participate in a brewery crawl without grimacing.
originStory: Rob and Kelly Horn moved here from New Jersey and started brewing in their garage before taking over a warehouse space near the airport. Named after their three kids (the 'three horns'), they brew approachable, dangerously drinkable beers like the 'Strawberry Golden Ale' that convert even non-beer drinkers.
address: 8036 River Dr SE #203, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Rainwater Brewing
description: A small-batch brewery focused on high-quality, approachable beers in a relaxed, family-friendly environment.
vibe: Relaxed and community-focused brewing space.
insiderVibe: Rainwater is the neighborhood's living room. It's often quieter than the big downtown spots, which makes it perfect for a long conversation over a sample flight. The brewers are almost always around and love to talk shop. The outdoor space is a hidden gem.
originStory: Founded by local brewing enthusiasts with a passion for the Pacific Northwest's rich water resources, Rainwater Brewing seeks to capture the essence of the region in every pint.
address: 2442 Mottman Rd SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, USA

name: Mount Olympus Brewing (Tumwater Taps)
vibe: The District Anchor; Aberdeen Grit
insiderVibe: Aberdeen grit in a polished Tumwater building. Rowdy in a good way, designed for loud laughs and big groups.
originStory: A martial arts-loving brewery from Aberdeen that decided to conquer the valley. They are the new anchor of the Tumwater Craft District.
address: 4242 Capitol Blvd SE Suite 100, Olympia, WA 98502, USA

name: Top Rung Brewing Company
vibe: The Outpost; precision and brotherhood
insiderVibe: It's in a warehouse district in Lacey. It's not 'cool' in the hipster sense, but it's honest. It's where you go after a shift. I respect it. No pretense.
originStory: Founded by Casey Sobol and Jason Stoltz, two career firefighters who spent their downtime perfecting recipes, this Lacey brewery is built on service, precision, and the brotherhood of the firehouse. It's an unpretentious warehouse taproom where the 'My Dog Scout Stout' has won more medals than most generals.
address: 8343 Hogum Bay Ln NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Sandstone Distillery
vibe: The Pilgrimage; Rugged and Authentic
insiderVibe: A world-class educational stop. The bacon whiskey is a conversation starter, but the gin is the real deal.
originStory: John Bourdon built a shrine to Tenino's stone-carving history. Grain-to-glass ruggedness fueled by locally grown grain and cooled by rainwater.
address: 842 Wright Rd SE, Tenino, WA 98589, USA

name: Talking Cedar
vibe: The Monument; Sovereign Spirits
insiderVibe: It took an act of Congress to build this. A monument to sovereignty and spirits, partnering with Heritage to build a state-of-the-art facility.
originStory: The Chehalis Tribe fought to repeal an 1834 law banning distilleries on tribal land. It is a massive facility dedicated to craft and heritage.
address: 19770 Sargent Rd SW, Rochester, WA 98579, USA

name: Axis Meads
vibe: The Rare Drop; Spiced Honey Adventures
insiderVibe: Spicy habanero and ginger meads that drink like cocktails. Located in the heart of Lacey's industrial zone.
originStory: Born from the back room of the legendary Skep & Skein. Dave Ross crafts meads that destroy the cloyingly sweet stereotype.
address: 2633 Willamette Dr NE suite b, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Stottle Winery
vibe: The Industrial Anchor; Serious chemistry
insiderVibe: High quality product. Josh knows his chemistry. It appeals to the 'Wine Snob' demographic.
originStory: Josh Stottlemyer traded web development for winemaking, setting up shop in a Lacey industrial park to prove you don't need a chateau to make world-class Syrah. It's a serious winery for serious wine drinkers, stripping away the pretension to focus entirely on what's in the glass.
address: 2641 Willamette Dr NE ste e, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Medicine Creek Winery
vibe: The Hideaway; Stagecoach-stop fantasy
insiderVibe: Jim Myers (a dentist with a cowboy soul) transformed a potato barn into an 1800s New Orleans brothel-themed tasting room.
originStory: Operating in the Nisqually Valley, this is a stagecoach-stop fantasy come to life, pouring big, bold Washington reds.
address: 947 Old Pacific Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA

name: Elk Pond Craft Ales
vibe: The Easter Egg; Scavenger Hunt Target
insiderVibe: We can't send people to them. They don't exist as a venue. But we can gamify the hunt. 'Find the Elk'—extra points for checking in a pint of Elk Pond at a partner bar. It encourages exploration of other venues.
originStory: The 'Ghost Brewery' of Olympia. The Wilkinson family built a dedicated micro-brewery on their property in 2023, but they don't open their doors to the public. You have to hunt for their kegs at local taverns like Pints Barn or Character's Corner to taste their 'Gold Craft' creations.
address: Downtown Olympia (Ghost Brewery), WA 98501

name: The Brotherhood Lounge
vibe: Industrial grit, stiff drinks, and shuffleboard.
address: 119 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
historySnippet: Rumored entrance to the tunnels and Oly's oldest bar.

name: McCoy’s Tavern
vibe: The legendary downtown dive. No frills.
address: 418 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

special_events.title: The Olson Bros Band
special_events.description: Live Country Rock from the PNW.

vibe: Old school olympia. Great beer selection.
address: 410 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Shiny Prize
vibe: Mid-century modern aesthetic with top-tier cocktails.
address: 118 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Nicole's Bar
description: A popular downtown spot known for its welcoming atmosphere, great food, and spacious outdoor patio. Nicole's is a go-to for sports fans and those looking for a buzzing vibe.
vibe: Active and welcoming with a great neighborhood feel.
insiderVibe: Nicole's is where the locals go. It's got that perfect balance of being a sports bar without being *just* a sports bar. The patio is one of the best in town, and the staff actually knows your name. It's unpretentious and consistently good.
originStory: Established as a cornerstone of the downtown Olympia bar scene, Nicole's has built a reputation for its inclusivity and commitment to providing a top-tier experience for every guest.
address: 109 Legion Way SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Cryptatropa Bar
vibe: Goth-industrial haven. Dark and moody.
address: 421 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Jake’s on 4th
vibe: Classic bar returned to its roots.
address: 311 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

vibe: Upscale cocktails and lounge atmosphere.
address: 404 Washington St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Cheeky Martini Lounge
vibe: Martinis and music.
address: 404 Washington St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Oly Taproom
vibe: Massive selection of taps by the water.
address: 312 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Swing Wine Bar
description: An award-winning wine and cocktail bar perched above Capitol Lake, offering a sophisticated yet comfortable atmosphere and an extensive selection of wines and spirits.
vibe: Sophisticated and romantic with exceptional views.
insiderVibe: Swing is the best 'date night' spot in Olympia, period. The view of Capitol Lake at sunset from the patio is unbeatable. It feels grown-up without being stuffy. The cocktail program is just as strong as the wine list—don't sleep on their seasonal specials.
originStory: Born from a love of fine wine and great company, Swing has become an Olympia landmark, celebrated for its curated cellar and elevated small plates.
address: 825 Columbia St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Rumors Wine Bar
vibe: Cozy spot for wine lovers.
address: 430 Washington St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: The Wine Loft
description: Serving up wine and smiles to Olympia and beyond. We offer a uniquely curated selection of retail wine with an emphasis on small-production winemakers from the US and around the globe. Join us for tastings every Saturday from 12-5!
vibe: Intimate loft setting for curated wine tastings and retail.
insiderVibe: The Wine Loft is one of those 'if you know, you know' spots. It's upstairs, quiet, and absolutely packed with character. Maggie and the team are incredibly knowledgeable—this isn't a place for mass-produced labels. It's for finding that one bottle you'll remember for years. Their Saturday tastings are a local institution.
originStory: A cornerstone of the downtown Olympia wine scene, The Wine Loft has dedicated years to championing independent winemakers and providing a sophisticated sanctuary for wine lovers.
address: 401 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Legends Arcade
vibe: Retro arcade games and beer.
address: 109 State Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: The Cove
vibe: Local favorite.
address: 311 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: McMenamins Spar Cafe
vibe: Historic McMenamins vibe.
address: 114 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
historySnippet: Sit in the original booths where the loggers drank.

name: Hannah's Bar & Grill
description: A legendary downtown Olympia fixture since 1935, Hannah's offers classic pub fare, a massive selection of spirits, and a vibe that's unchanged by time (in the best way possible).
vibe: Classic American grill with a thick layer of local history.
insiderVibe: Hannah's is the definition of a 'comfortable' bar. It's where you go when you want a solid burger, a stiff drink, and to be surrounded by generations of Olympia history. It's high-energy on game days and karaoke nights, but welcoming every single day of the week.
originStory: Opening its doors in 1935, Hannah's has survived prohibition's end, several world changes, and countless downtown shifts, remaining a steady beacon of hospitality in the heart of the city.
address: 123 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

vibe: Ghost
address: 3442 180th Ave SW, Tenino, WA 98589, USA

name: The Mark Olympia
description: An elegant Italian-inspired restaurant and bar known for its organic ingredients, refined cocktails, and beautiful courtyard dining.
vibe: Elegant, organic, and sophisticated.
insiderVibe: The Mark is where you go when you want to feel a bit fancy. The courtyard is arguably the most beautiful dining space in Olympia. Their commitment to organic and local ingredients isn't just talk—you can taste it in the food and the drinks. Perfect for a celebration or a high-end night out.
originStory: Dedicated to the principles of organic cooking and sustainable hospitality, The Mark has been a pioneer in Olympia's fine dining scene for years.
address: 407 Columbia St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

vibe: Historic and elevated dining with a dedicated bar.

name: The Pig Bar
vibe: A local favorite for drinks and a solid bar menu.

name: The Oyster House
vibe: Waterfront dining with a legendary oyster bar.

name: Skep and Skein
vibe: Mead, cider, and beer in a cozy, intellectual atmosphere.

name: Two Mile House
vibe: Classic neighborhood bar with local roots.

name: Buzz's Bar and Grill
vibe: Rowdy, fun, and serves some of the best bar food in town.

name: The Iron Rabbit
vibe: Gastropub excellence with a fantastic cocktail program.

name: Cascadia Grill
vibe: Eclectic menu and a warm, woody bar atmosphere.

name: Charro Mexican Restaurant
vibe: Authentic Mexican flavors in a vibrant, artistic space.
insiderVibe: The outdoor seating is a must on a sunny day. Their daily happy hour from 2-5pm is one of the better kept secrets on the east side.
address: 1720 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA

name: Chelsea Farms Oyster Bar
vibe: Tide-to-table excellence in a chic, marine-inspired market space.
insiderVibe: Second-generation shellfish farmers who know exactly what they're doing. The 21+ lounge area is perfect for escaping the market bustle for a focused cocktail and a dozen Chelsea Gems.
address: 222 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: 23 Kitchens
vibe: The ultimate sports and socialization hub, featuring pickleball, rotisserie-style eats, and a self-serve tap wall.
insiderVibe: The rooftop bar is the real MVP here. They use vertical rotisserie ovens since they have no fryers, so expect great sandwiches and tacos instead of the usual greasy appetizers. Plus, 11 pickleball courts means the energy is always high.
address: 2440 Marvin Road NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Insert Coin (Olympia/Lacey)
vibe: Nostalgic retro gaming meets modern craft beer and elevated bar fare.
insiderVibe: The local version of the Centralia legend. Over 100 games, a self-pour tap wall, and burgers that actually hold their own. It transforms into 21+ after 11 PM, so plan your child-free session accordingly.
address: 3430 Pacific Ave SE Ste D1, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Pints Barn
vibe: Rustic charm and local brotherhood; your 'home away from home' in Tumwater.
insiderVibe: Order the oversized pretzel with beer cheese—it's a religious experience. The circular bar makes it easy to make friends, and the patio is arguably the best all-season outdoor space in the county.
address: 114 E St SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Pints & Quarts
vibe: Funky, local vibe with plenty of quirky memorabilia and a killer Bloody Mary bar.
insiderVibe: Wednesdays are the move—free BBQ with a drink purchase. It's a true neighborhood hub where everyone from military members to working pros and older couples rubs elbows. Very welcoming.
address: 1230 College St SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: River's Edge
vibe: Premier sports bar and dining at the Tumwater Valley Golf Club.
insiderVibe: The state-of-the-art setup makes it the best place in Tumwater to watch football. Don't sleep on the Dungeness Crab Cakes or their weekend breakfast menu.
address: 4611 Tumwater Valley Drive SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Beat Drop Kitchen & Event Center
vibe: All-ages restaurant by day, high-energy dance destination by night.
insiderVibe: They have 6,000 square feet of space. Wednesday is for country/line dancing, Friday is Latin/Salsa, and Saturday is the full club experience. The VIP booths with champagne are a nice touch for groups.
address: 1225 Ruddell Rd SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: Cup of Swords Tavern
vibe: A permanent Renaissance Faire taproom where fantasy meets flavor.
insiderVibe: Sundays are D&D days. Feel free to 'garb up'—they love it when people come in themed attire. They don't have a kitchen, but they're adjacent to Axis Meads and let you bring in your own food.
address: 1005 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Hops on the Hill
vibe: Texas-style BBQ and craft beer haven in the South Sound.
insiderVibe: The brisket is the real deal. Tuesdays are trivia nights, and they're one of the few places in Tumwater with a serious focus on premium bourbons alongside their craft tap list.
address: 1870 Barnes Blvd SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, USA

name: The Office Tavern
vibe: The local legend remodeled; friendly, community-focused, and 21+ only.
insiderVibe: The 10-foot screen is a sports fan's dream. No kids allowed, ever. Their 'Office Hour' (Happy Hour) runs all day Monday, which is the perfect way to start the week.
address: 2030 Mottman Road SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, USA

name: State & Central
vibe: A community hub in the heart of working-class Olympia history.
insiderVibe: The 'Juicy Lucy' is the local legend here. Weekend brunch is sneaky good, especially if you snag a spot on the sidewalk patio on a sunny morning. It's the ultimate neighborhood decompression zone.
address: 1415 State Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA

name: The Boulevard Tavern
vibe: Unpretentious, spacious, and deeply rooted in the Eastside community.
insiderVibe: Barstool Bingo on Wednesdays is mandatory local lore. Don't be fooled by the modest exterior; it's huge inside. The covered smoking area and free pool Sundays make it a classic reliable hangout.
address: 2221 Pacific Ave SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Northwest Beerwerks
vibe: Hip, relaxed taproom vibes in a beautifully renovated vintage home.
insiderVibe: With 32 taps and a massive selection of bottles, this is a gearhead's paradise for beer. The outdoor yard is one of the best spots in town to hang with your dog. No kitchen, so check the food truck schedule or BYO.
address: 420 Steele St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: The Town Tavern
vibe: A genuine neighborhood dive where everyone actually knows your name.
insiderVibe: The definition of a 'hidden' bar on Pacific. It's got that perfect upbeat vibe with friendly bartenders who don't take any nonsense. Great for a quiet beer or a few rounds of pool away from the downtown noise.
address: 2020 Pacific Ave SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: The Viking Lounge
vibe: High-energy dive bar with legendary karaoke and one of the best cheap breakfasts in Lacey.
insiderVibe: Their margaritas are deceptively strong and remarkably good for a dive. Early bird breakfast (8-10am) is the best way to start a weekday. Stay late for the karaoke crowd—it's always a show.
address: 6318 Martin Way E, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: O'Blarney's Irish Pub
vibe: A massive, vibrant blend of traditional Irish spirits and local sports energy.
insiderVibe: The Blarney Burger is an essential Olympia food group. They have a great balance between a quiet family dining area and a high-octane sports bar. Check out their Irish jam sessions for the real authentic feel.
address: 4411 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98516, USA

name: Firecreek Alehouse
vibe: Rustic lodge aesthetics with sweeping views of the Capitol City Golf Club.
insiderVibe: The prime rib on Fridays and Saturdays is the main event. It feels like a mountain retreat right in the middle of Lacey. The patio overlooks the greens and is arguably the most peaceful place to have a beer in the county.
address: 5225 Yelm Hwy SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: Farrelli's Pizza (Tumwater)
vibe: Community-focused artisan pizza with a lively, family-friendly bar scene.
insiderVibe: Team Trivia on Wednesdays is the big draw and it gets packed. Their fire-pitting technique is no joke—the crust is some of the best in the South Sound. Great for groups and kids (they have a game room).
address: 111 Tumwater Blvd SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Farrelli's Pizza (Lacey)
vibe: The original wood-fired pioneer of the region; iconic, warm, and highly social.
insiderVibe: This was the first store (est. 1995) and it still holds that original wood-fired energy. They've got pull-tabs and pool on the bar side, making it a favorite for the after-work crowd as much as for families.
address: 4870 Yelm Highway, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: The Cedar Inn
vibe: Welcoming, down-to-earth tavern with a friendly country pulse.
insiderVibe: Best Bloody Marys in the Hawks Prairie corridor. It's a classic neighborhood spot where you can grab a Philly cheesesteak and some deep-fried mushrooms while playing a round of darts. It feels like a true community living room.
address: 9030 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98516, USA

name: Sampan Bar & Grill
vibe: An energetic fusion of Japanese cuisine and high-spirited nightlife.
insiderVibe: You have to try the 'Flaming Lemon Drop'—it's their signature move. A historic landmark since 1978, it's one of the few places in the area where you can transition seamlessly from sushi to a packed dance floor with karaoke.
address: 922 Hensley St NE, Olympia, WA 98516, USA

name: Old Hwy 99 Company Bar & Grill
vibe: A massive, welcoming roadside retreat featuring high-quality scratch cooking.
insiderVibe: The brisket and chicken fried steak are top-tier. Even though it's technically in Tenino, it's a mandatory stop for the south-county crowd. The metal outdoor building with heaters makes it a great year-round spot for a beer.
address: 12743 Old Hwy 99 SE, Tenino, WA 98589, USA

name: The Westside Tavern
vibe: A local Olympia dive with a 'Cheers' heart and some of the best pub food in the region.
insiderVibe: The 'Slayer Burger' (bacon + avocado) and their award-winning Tavern Burger are non-negotiable. It's owned by the same folks as Hash, so you know the quality is there despite the low-key dive atmosphere. Eclectic, warm, and very local.
address: 1815 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA

name: Puget Sound Taps
vibe: A locally owned tap house with a massive rotating selection and friendly service.
insiderVibe: 34 beverages on tap means you'll always find something new. Their pizza is surprisingly legit for a taproom, and their 'Monthly Special Pizza' is always worth a look. Pet-friendly and great for group beers.
address: 4250 Martin Way E Ste 101, Olympia, WA 98507, USA

name: The Nocturnal Hound
vibe: A cozy, sophisticated wine bar and bottle shop specializing in local gems.
insiderVibe: Opened in 2024, it's the newest crown jewel of Tumwater's social scene. Amazing focus on WA/OR wines, mead, and cider. Their charcuterie boards and burrata are the perfect sophisticated pairing for a quiet rainy evening.
address: 324 Custer Way SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: O'Malley's Lounge
vibe: A laid-back Westside staple attached to the bowling alley, perfect for sports and groups.
insiderVibe: Hidden next to Westside Lanes. 16 TVs and two projectors make it one of the most reliable places to catch a game. They have live music frequently and a surprisingly spacious outdoor area for a bowling alley lounge.
address: 2200 Garfield Ave NW Ste 1, Olympia, WA 98502, USA

name: Fatso's Bar & Grill
vibe: Friendly, old-school bar and grill focused on home-cooked favorites and community.
insiderVibe: Their clam chowder is award-winning for a reason—don't skip it. It's a very chill, family-owned vibe where the service is as warm as the homemade soups. Great low-key spot for a burger and a game.
address: 3420 Pacific Ave SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Pealo's Bar (Nisqually Red Wind Casino)
vibe: Sophisticated cocktails in the heart of the Red Wind action.
insiderVibe: The centerpiece of the casino. Perfect for high-end spirits and watching the floor energy from a plush seat.
address: 12819 Yelm Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA

name: Coho Sports Lounge (Nisqually Red Wind Casino)
vibe: The South Sound's premier casino sports destination.
insiderVibe: Wall-to-wall screens and a dedicated sportsbook vibe. If you want to watch the game while surrounded by casino energy, this is the spot.
address: 12819 Yelm Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA

name: River Water Bar and Grille (Nisqually Red Wind Casino)
vibe: Elegant dining featuring Northwest favorites and casino luxury.
insiderVibe: Their seafood selection is impressive. It brings a touch of fine dining to the casino floor without losing the approachable Northwest feel.
address: 12819 Yelm Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA

name: Legends Sports Bar (Lucky Eagle Casino)
vibe: High-energy sports gaming and classic bar favorites.
insiderVibe: The local hub for major fight nights and game days. Great energy and quick service for those on a hot streak.
address: 12888 188th Ave SW, Rochester, WA 98579, USA

name: Crafthouse Wood Fired Pizza (Lucky Eagle Casino)
vibe: Artisanal wood-fired pizza and a solid craft tap list.
insiderVibe: Surprisingly high-quality pizza for a casino environment. It's the perfect spot for a more relaxed meal away from the slots.
address: 12888 188th Ave SW, Rochester, WA 98579, USA

name: Room 188 (Lucky Eagle Casino)
vibe: Premium steakhouse experience and refined atmosphere.
insiderVibe: The sophisticated choice at Lucky Eagle. Excellent steaks and a curated wine list for those celebrating a big win.
address: 12888 188th Ave SW, Rochester, WA 98579, USA

name: The Riverbend Restaurant (Fortune Casino)
vibe: Diverse menu and classic casino hospitality in Lacey.
insiderVibe: One of the few spots in Lacey where you can get a full menu of Asian-inspired dishes and classic American fare until late. Very friendly service.
address: 8318 Quinault Dr NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Littlerock Saloon
vibe: A true rustic saloon with deep roots in the Littlerock community.
insiderVibe: If you want that authentic out-in-the-country feel, this is it. Honest drinks, friendly locals, and a vibe that hasn't changed in decades.
address: 6524 128th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98512, USA

name: MEXTIZA By: El Serape
vibe: Elevated Mexican dining experience with a modern Lacey twist.
insiderVibe: Formerly the Lacey El Serape, now rebranded as Mextiza. It still has the legendary recipes but with a fresh, updated energy and an expanded cocktail program.
address: 8200 Quinault Dr NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: The Mayan Family Mexican Restaurant (Pacific Ave)
vibe: Classic family hospitality and hearty Mexican tradition on Pacific Ave.
insiderVibe: A local institution. The portions are huge and the salsa has that exact consistent heat that locals have loved for years.
address: 4520 Pacific Ave SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: The Mayan Family Mexican Restaurant (Yelm Hwy)
vibe: Warm, welcoming Mexican dining center in the Yelm Hwy corridor.
insiderVibe: A favorite for the south Lacey/Tumwater crowd. It carries that same consistent Mayan quality and is always a reliable spot for a large group.
address: 4820 Yelm Hwy SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: The Mayan Family Mexican Restaurant (Marvin Rd)
vibe: Authentic Mexican flavors serving the Hawks Prairie community.
insiderVibe: Perfectly situated for the north Lacey commuters. It's the newest of the three and maintains the high standard of the Mayan brand.
address: 8125 Marvin Rd NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: La Patrona
vibe: A vibrant and authentic taste of Mexico in the heart of Tumwater.
insiderVibe: Often overlooked but shouldn't be. Their tacos are legit and the atmosphere is always lively and welcoming.
address: 5212 Capitol Blvd SE Unit A, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: The Ram Restaurant & Brewery (Lacey)
vibe: A sprawling sports hub with local brews and award-winning burgers.
insiderVibe: The 'Buttface Amber' is the classic move here. It's a massive space that can handle the biggest sports crowds in Lacey. Consistent and reliable.
address: 8100 Freedom Ln NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA

name: Ricardo's Kitchen and Bar
vibe: Sophisticated dining and exceptional dry-aged beef in the heart of Lacey.
insiderVibe: Rick Nelsen's masterpiece. The dry-aged 'Sexy Beef' is the best steak in the county, period. The bar program is equally sophisticated.
address: 676 Woodland Square Loop SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: Plaza Jalisco
vibe: Authentic and welcoming Mexican tradition in the Tumwater corridor.
insiderVibe: A reliable neighborhood staple for years. It's a classic spot where you can always count on consistent food and friendly service.
address: 5212 Capitol Blvd SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA

name: Nisqually Bar & Grill
vibe: A welcoming blend of family grill and high-energy local pub.
insiderVibe: Directly off I-5 exit 114. The sports memorabilia collection is incredible, and the 19 beers on tap make it a premier stop for travelers and locals alike.
address: 10323 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98516, USA

name: The Mark
vibe: Intimate, artistic Italian dining with deep roots and authentic Roman style.
insiderVibe: A woman-owned gem since 2001. The Roman-style pizza and curated Italian wine list are unmatched. It's cash-only, so come prepared for manual elegance.
address: 407 Columbia Street SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Valentina's Lounge
vibe: A romantic, vibrant Latin-inspired escape in the heart of downtown.
insiderVibe: The intimate seating around fireplaces and fountains makes it arguably the best date night spot in Olympia. The tequila and mezcal program is elite.
address: 325 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Row
vibe: Vibrant waterfront dining at the edge of historic Percival Landing.
insiderVibe: The waterfront patio is the best place to be in the summer. Their seafood focus and local craft bar program capture the essence of the South Sound perfectly.
address: 208 State Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA

name: Stack 571 Burger & Whiskey Bar
vibe: A refined burger experience with a global whiskey library.
insiderVibe: The 'Stackhouse' is the anchor of the mall's dining wing. Gourmet burgers and a whiskey selection that rivals anything downtown. The waffle fries with gorgonzola sauce are a local legend.
address: 625 Black Lake Blvd SW Suite 530, Olympia, WA 98502, USA

name: Landmark Tavern
vibe: An authentic hometown bar in Tenino with legacy spanning over a century.
insiderVibe: Established in 1906, it still feels like the town's heartbeat. It holds its history in its wood and its stories. Perfect for a beer after exploring the Tenino quarries.
address: 313 Hodgden St S, Tenino, WA 98589, USA

name: Hops n Drops (Lacey)
vibe: A neighborhood gathering place known for its icy real-fruit drinks and hearty energy.
insiderVibe: The 'Icy Drops' are served in glasses that are literally made of ice. It's a high-energy community hub that's as good for families as it is for neighbors grabbing a drink.
address: 4739 Avery Lane SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA

name: The Brick on Trosper
vibe: A sprawling sports and family hub with a legendary brick oven.
insiderVibe: The 'Thick as a Brick' pizza is mandatory. It's the ultimate Tumwater hangout for a game or a large family meal. Welcoming, rustic, and always busy.
address: 709 Trosper Road SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, USA
